To prevent SQL Injection in the Java code snippet provided, you should use parameterized queries instead of concatenating user input directly into the SQL query string. Parameterized queries help prevent SQL Injection by treating user input as data rather than executable code.

Here is an updated version of the code snippet with proper security measures implemented:

